**Kullfi Kumarr Bajewala** (lit. Kullfi Kumarr Musician) is an
[Indian](/wiki/India "India") [musical](/wiki/Musical_film "Musical film")
[television series](/wiki/Television_series "Television series"), which is
premiere on [Star Plus](/wiki/Star_Plus "Star Plus") and stream on
[Hotstar](/wiki/Hotstar "Hotstar"). It features Aakriti Sharma, [Mohit
Malik](/wiki/Mohit_Malik "Mohit Malik"), [Anjali Anand](/wiki/Anjali_Anand
"Anjali Anand"), Myra Singh and Shruti Sharma.[2] This show is produced by
[Gul Khan](/wiki/Gul_Khan_\(producer\) "Gul Khan \(producer\)"), Karishma
Jain, Nilanjana Purkayasstha and Herumb Khot.[3][4] It is a remake version of
the [Bengali language](/wiki/Bengali_language "Bengali language") television
series _[Potol Kumar Gaanwala](/wiki/Potol_Kumar_Gaanwala "Potol Kumar
Gaanwala")_ , which was aired on [Star Jalsha](/wiki/Star_Jalsha "Star
Jalsha") in 2015.[5][6] The story revolves around the journey of a young
singing prodigy Kullfi,who encounters a lot can of worms to unite with her
father, Sikandar Singh Gill.[7]

##
Synopsis[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Kullfi_Kumarr_Bajewala&action=edit&section=1
"Edit section: Synopsis")]

Kullfi is an illegitimate daughter of Nimrat and popular singer Sikandar Singh
Gill. Sikandar had left Nimrat for his career and he is unaware of his
daughter. Kullfi is born as a singer but is unaware of her father. They are
living with her uncle, Sattu and aunt Nihalo, who hates them but Nihalo want
to encash of Kullfi's talent so she keeps them. Nimrat suffers from cancer so
Kullfi was taken to Sikandar by Bhalla to ask for help.

Sikandar is married to another woman, Lovely and has a daughter Amyra. Kullfi
meets Sikandar to ask for help but was not able to get due to the
circumstances. Nirmat, searching for Kullfi, and Sikandar cross each other on
the road but miss the glance. But suddenly Nirmat was hit by Lovely's car and
dies.

Few days later, Kullfi runs way from her aunt's home and accidentally reaches
to Sikandar's house and Lovely keeps her and decides to use her talent to make
Amyra a successful singer.

###
Development[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Kullfi_Kumarr_Bajewala&action=edit&section=6
"Edit section: Development")]

On 14 February 2018, the first promo of the show was released, with the title
song. On 28 February 2018, the second promo of the show was released which is
based on Kullfi, wished [Happy Holi](/wiki/Holi "Holi"). On 24 February 2018,
child artiste Aakriti Sharma and actress Shruti Sharma welcomed the production
team, media and public with colours of Holi, location at
[Lucknow](/wiki/Lucknow "Lucknow").[14][3] Currently, this show set in
[Mumbai](/wiki/Mumbai "Mumbai") and [Pathankot](/wiki/Pathankot "Pathankot").
On 10 March 2018, a musical concert was organized by Gul Khan at
[Chandigarh](/wiki/Chandigarh "Chandigarh"), [Punjab](/wiki/Punjab "Punjab").
The musical concert was performed by child artiste Aakriti Sharma, Punjabi
singer and songwriter, [Gurdas Maan](/wiki/Gurdas_Maan "Gurdas Maan"), the
[Nooran Sisters](/wiki/Nooran_Sisters "Nooran Sisters") and
[Rajasthani](/wiki/Rajasthani_people "Rajasthani people") young maestros, the
Langa Kids.[15][16]

###
Casting[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Kullfi_Kumarr_Bajewala&action=edit&section=7
"Edit section: Casting")]

The show's main characters, Kullfi and Sikandar Singh Gill, were the core of
the concept for Kullfi Kumarr Bajewala.[17] These characters are taken from
original television series [Potol Kumar Gaanwala](/wiki/Potol_Kumar_Gaanwala
"Potol Kumar Gaanwala")'s Poteshwari and Sujon Kumar Malik. Kullfi child
character's role is played by Aakriti Sharma. She was selected for her acting
talent. Producer Nilanjana Purkayasstha said, "Aakriti is a very enthusiastic
and fearless child."[18][19] Otherside, Amaira character's role was decided to
play by [Spandan Chaturvedi](/wiki/Spandan_Chaturvedi "Spandan Chaturvedi")
but due to date issues, she was replaced by Myra Singh. Myra said, "It's my
first time on television and I'm really excited to play this role."[20] Actor
Mohit Malik said about his role, "I have the signature rockstar look in Kullfi
Kumarr Bajewala."[21][22] [Dhhai Kilo Prem](/wiki/Dhhai_Kilo_Prem "Dhhai Kilo
Prem")'s actress, Anjali Anand is playing Lovely Kaur character, who is
Amyra's mother. She said, "Character matters the most to me and this character
is extremely challenging and fun at the same time."[23][24] Aakriti's brother,
Hardik Sharma will going to join this show, debut as Kullfi's friend. He is
also talented like her sister that's why producer Gul Khan and Nilanjana
select him. Aakriti said, "I'm so happy to see Hardik. I am meeting him after
three months."[25][26] [27] [Barun Sobti](/wiki/Barun_Sobti "Barun Sobti"),
who was recently played on Gul Khan's [Iss Pyaar Ko Kya Naam Doon
3](/wiki/Iss_Pyaar_Ko_Kya_Naam_Doon_3 "Iss Pyaar Ko Kya Naam Doon 3"), will be
playing on this show debut as a Rockstar, Sikandar's competitor and Amyra's
music teacher role.[28] According to source, "Gul wanted to Barun in a
significant role for this show. The makers are in talks to get Barun on
board."[29] [28] Barun said, "It is exhausting. I am back in the grind. So we
are in that zone where we are putting in everything that we have and hoping
that people will like it."[30][31]

### Critical
reception[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Kullfi_Kumarr_Bajewala&action=edit&section=10
"Edit section: Critical reception")]

[Nimki Mukhiya](/wiki/Nimki_Mukhiya "Nimki Mukhiya")'s actress aka Bhumika
Gurung wrote about Aakriti Sharma, "With this super talented and super cute
little bunny of Kullfi Kumarr Bajewala."[37] [Ye Hai
Mohabbatein](/wiki/Ye_Hai_Mohabbatein "Ye Hai Mohabbatein")'s actress Santoshi
aka Shahnaz Rizwan said, "The girl’s acting is very good. She is too talented.
The direction of the show is very good and realistic."[38] Sreejeeta Sen of
Bollywood Life wrote: "While the show failed to create an impact with its
launch, but now the show seems like a dark horse of the race."[39] Akriti
Sharma's mother, Dimple Sharma says, "Akrit showed keen interest in creative
arts since a very young age. But we will not compromise on her education.
Akriti gets time to play on the sets, if her shot is not ready."[40] [News
Nation](/wiki/News_Nation "News Nation") wrote: "Kullfi Kumarr Bajewala has
done wonders since the time it was released."[41]

###
Ratings[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Kullfi_Kumarr_Bajewala&action=edit&section=11
"Edit section: Ratings")]

In the first week, this show was ranked in the top sixteen in India.[42] This
show has received a pretty good number of [Target rating
point](/wiki/Target_rating_point "Target rating point"), 4323 impressions.
Which means more than 4.3 million viewers are watched this show in the first
week.[43][44] This show was ranked in the top one in the [United
Kingdom](/wiki/United_Kingdom "United Kingdom"). More than 98,000 viewers
watched this show in the UK. Kullfi Kumarr Bajewala was taken [Yeh Hai
Mohabbatein](/wiki/Yeh_Hai_Mohabbatein "Yeh Hai Mohabbatein") position, which
was previously at the top one in the UK.[45] During the third week, this show
has entered into the top ten with eighth position, 4.8 million impressions in
India.[39] During the sixth week, this show has archived sixth position in
India.[46] During the seventh week, this show has reached at the top fifth
position with 4500 impressions.[47][48]

##
Release[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Kullfi_Kumarr_Bajewala&action=edit&section=12
"Edit section: Release")]

The show replaced the time slot of [Ikyawann](/wiki/Ikyawann "Ikyawann"), but
Panorama Entertainment's production producer Suzana Ghai has confirmed that
Ikyawann was not going to air off, it was replaced the time slot of [Meri
Durga](/wiki/Meri_Durga "Meri Durga"), which was aired off.[49][50][51] On 19
March 2018, The show first released on the [Hotstar](/wiki/Hotstar "Hotstar")
streaming service, for the premium viewers of India. Later, this show
broadcast on the [Star Plus](/wiki/Star_Plus "Star Plus"). Asian countries
like [Bangladesh](/wiki/Bangladesh "Bangladesh"), [Indonesia](/wiki/Indonesia
"Indonesia"), [Malaysia](/wiki/Malaysia "Malaysia"), [Myanmar](/wiki/Myanmar
"Myanmar"), [Nepal](/wiki/Nepal "Nepal"), [Pakistan](/wiki/Pakistan
"Pakistan"), [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore "Singapore") and [Sri
Lanka](/wiki/Sri_Lanka "Sri Lanka") broadcast on the original release date. On
20 March 2018, the show was released in United Kingdom and United States.[52]
